President Donald J. Trump met with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman of Saudi Arabia to review progress in strengthening the American-Saudi bilateral relationship. They discussed finalizing new commercial deals that would create over 120,000 American jobs and support Saudi Arabia's economic reform agenda. The Crown Prince thanked the President for American leadership in defeating ISIS and countering Iran's actions in the Middle East. They also discussed the threat posed by the Houthis in Yemen, supported by the Iranian Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps, and agreed on the need for a political resolution to the conflict. President Trump expressed his anticipation for the visit of King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud to the United States later this year.